contentrichtext.text: '''David Price''' may refer to: {{tocright}} ==Military== *[[David Price (East India Company officer)]] (1762–1835), East India Company officer and orientalist *[[David Price (Royal Navy officer)]] (1790–1854), British Rear Admiral at the Siege of Petropavlovsk == Politics == *Sir [[David Price (British politician)]] (born 1924), British Conservative Member of Parliament in the 1970s and 1980s *[[David Price (Canadian politician)]] (born 1945), Member of Parliament from Quebec *[[David Price (U.S. politician)]] (born 1940), Democratic Congressman representing the 4th district of North Carolina *[[David Edward Price]] (1826–1883), Canadian businessman and Senator == Sports == *[[David Price (baseball)]] (born 1985), pitcher for the Tampa Bay Rays *[[David Price (boxer)]] (born 1983), British Commonwealth heavyweight champion *[[David Price (footballer)]] (born 1955), football player for Arsenal F.C. *[[David Price (soccer)]] (born 1971), English soccer player and coach in the United States *[[David Price Racing]], British auto racing team founded by David Price. ==Other== *[[David Price (actor)]] (born 1963), American film and television actor *[[David Price (Australian actor)]], Australian actor in ''[[All Men Are Liars]]'' *[[David Price (director)]] (born 1961), American director of ''[[Children of the Corn II: The Final Sacrifice]]'' and ''[[Son of Darkness: To Die For II]]'' *[[David Price (anthropologist)]] (born 1960), American anthropologist *[[David Price (British academic)]] (born 1956), British earth scientist at University College London *[[David Price (musician)]] (born 1969), British choral conductor and organist *[[David Price (producer)]], producer of Screamfeeder's ''[[Burn Out Your Name]]'' *[[David Price (news anchor)]], on [[WTAJ-TV]] *[[Dave Price (publisher)]] (born 1962), American journalist *[[Dave Price]] (born 1966), reporter {{hndis|Price, David}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Price, David}} [[sv:David Price]]
